<table border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1>
	<tr>
		<td valign=middle align=left width=22><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=1 width=20 border=0></td>
		<td valign=middle align=right class="header">Form Wizard</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2"><hr size="1"></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text">Form Wizard allows the creation of "forms on-the-fly" with no programming skill required. It can be used to create any type of web forms that are used to gather data from the website/intranet users.</td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">Submitting A Form</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the form and fill in all the compulsory fields.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Submit</strong> button to submit the form. Click on <strong>Save As Draft</strong> button to save the form without submitting</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">Form Approval Cycle</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">After you have submitted a form that requires approval, your form will be listed in the <strong>Submitted Form Status</strong>.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">A notification message will be sent to the immediate approver of this form. In the meantime, you are able to view the submission details, However, it cannot be edited.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">3.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">The approver is able to approve and view the form details by accessing the <strong>Submitted From Approval</strong> link. Clicking on the form application will display the form details.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">4.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Approve</strong> button to approve the application, or <strong>Reject</strong> button to reject it.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">Resubmiting Rejected Submission</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Once the approver has rejected your submission, you will receive a notification message.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">In <strong>Submitted Form Status</strong> link, click on the form to view the details.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">3.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Resubmit</strong> button and the form will be listed in the <strong>Draft Submission</strong> link. You are able to edit the submission.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
